{{Infobox glacier | name = Academy Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | type = | location = [[Pensacola Mountains]] | coordinates = {{coord|84|15|S|61|00|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Academy Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | terminus = [[Foundation Ice Stream]] | status = unknown }}
'''Academy Glacier''' ({{coord|84|15|S|061|00|W|type:glacier_region:AQ|display=inline}}) is a major [[Antarctica|Antarctic]] [[glacier]] in the [[Pensacola Mountains]], draining northwestward between the [[Patuxent Range|Patuxent]] and [[Neptune Range|Neptune]] [[mountain range|ranges]] to enter [[Foundation Ice Stream]].
It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey|USGS]] from surveys and US Navy air photos in 1956-66, and was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names|US-ACAN]] for the [[United States National Academy of Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]] which played an important role in the planning of the U.S. program in Antarctica.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://geographic.org/geographic_names/antname.php?uni=36&fid=antgeo_101|title=Academy Glacier, Antarctica|website=Geographical Names|publisher=|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
