{{Infobox journal | title = Cakalele | cover = | discipline = Cultural and ethnic studies | abbreviation =Cakalele | frequency = annual | website = http://hdl.handle.net/10125/3124 | publisher = [[University of Hawaii at Manoa|University of Hawaii at Manoa Center for Southeast Asian Studies]] | country = [[United States]] | history = 1990-2000 | ISSN = 1053-2285 | eISSN = }} '''''Cakalele:''''' ''Maluku Research Journal/Majalah Penelitian Maluku'' is an academic journal that publishes the results of research about [[Maluku Islands|Maluku]] and Maluku communities in Indonesia and the Netherlands. The journal chronicles the growth of Maluku in humanities and the sciences as it expands geographically. ''Cakalele'' is stored on the [[ScholarSpace]] institutional repository of the [[University of Hawaii]] at [[Manoa]]. The journal was founded by linguist James T. Collins.<ref name="Rauch1995">{{cite book |last1=Rauch |first1=Irmengard |last2=Moore |first2=Cornelia Niekus |date=1995 |title=Across the Oceans: Studies from East to West in honor of Richard K. Seymour |publisher=University of Hawaii Press |isbn=0-8248-1693-5 }}</ref>
